Discovery

01

I’ll dive deep into your personal goals and long-term vision

  • Initial Consultation:

    Understand the client’s vision, goals, and target audience.

  • Research:

    Analyze competitors and industry trends to gather insights.

  • Define Scope:

    Set the project’s objectives, deliverables, and timelines.

/3-5 days/

Design

/

02

I'll create mockups that bring your brand to life

  • Wireframing:

    Create low-fidelity wireframes to map out the site’s structure.

  • Style Guide Creation:

    Develop a design language including colors, fonts, and UI elements.

  • Prototype Development:

    Build clickable prototypes for client feedback.

  • Finalize Design:

    Approve the final design with detailed mockups for all pages.

/1-2 weeks/

Build

/

03

Using no-code tools, I'll construct your site

  • Page Construction:

    Build out the website structure using selected tools.

  • Content Integration:

    Import and format content (text, images, videos).

  • Basic SEO Setup:

    Optimize on-page elements for search engines.

/1 week/

Launch

/

04

Your site goes live, ready to make an impact

  • Client Review:

    Present the site to the client for feedback.

  • Revisions:

    Make necessary changes based on client feedback.

/2-3 days/

{09} — FAQ

Got Questions?

01/

What is your typical project timeline?

The timeline for a project typically ranges from 4 to 8 weeks, depending on the scope and complexity. After an initial consultation, I’ll provide a detailed timeline with key milestones so you know what to expect at each stage.

02/

Do you offer ongoing maintenance and support?

Yes, I offer ongoing maintenance and support packages to ensure your website stays updated and runs smoothly. This includes updates, bug fixes, and any necessary changes as your business grows.

03/

Can you work with existing brand guidelines?

Absolutely! I’m experienced in working with existing brand guidelines to ensure your website aligns with your established identity. I can seamlessly incorporate your branding while enhancing your digital presence.

04/

How do you handle revisions and feedback?

Revisions and feedback are a crucial part of the process. I typically offer a set number of revision rounds to refine the design based on your input. I ensure clear communication throughout, so your vision is brought to life effectively.
